"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451306","Department of Health","false","2016-02-11","<p>Shortly, we will be engaging colleagues across Government on the proposed changes to housing benefit. As the cross-Government lead, the Department for Work and Pensions is coordinating any work to understand the likely impact of the reforms.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","26292","2016-02-11T14:03:20.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451306/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451306/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451306/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-02-08","Housing Benefit: Supported Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 5 February 2016 to Question 25549, if he will have discussions with the Secretary of State for (a) Work and Pensions, (b) Communities and Local Government and (c) other Government departments on proposed changes to housing benefit for tenants in supported housing; and if he will make an estimate of the number of people likely to be affected by the proposed change.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","26289"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451307","Department of Health","false","2016-02-11","<p>NHS England will begin the collection and analysis of responses from services in March. Following final sign off, NHS England expect to publish the benchmarking tool no later than June 2016.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2016-02-11T13:59:52.71Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451307/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451307/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451307/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-02-08","Mental Health Services: Ethnic Groups","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 8 February 2016 to Question 25729, when he plans to (a) complete the BAME benchmarking pilot and (b) publish the benchmarking tool.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","26290"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451308","Department of Health","false","2016-02-11","<p>The Department did not submit any evidence to HM Treasury to inform the decision to cap housing benefit for those in supported housing, announced in the Spending Review 2015.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2016-02-11T16:10:41.65Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451308/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451308/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451308/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-02-08","Housing Benefit: Supported Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the evidential basis provided by his Department to HM Treasury was to inform the decision to cap housing benefit for people in supported housing.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","26291"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451309","Department of Health","false","2016-02-11","<p>Shortly, we will be engaging colleagues across Government on the proposed changes to housing benefit. As the cross-Government lead, the Department for Work and Pensions is coordinating any work to understand the likely impact of the reforms.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","26289","2016-02-11T14:03:20.71Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451309/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451309/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451309/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-02-08","Housing Benefit: Supported Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether he has made an assessment of the effect of proposed changes to housing benefit on tenants in supported housing and their access to mental health services.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","26292"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451310","Department of Health","false","2016-02-11","<p>The Government has invested over £1.5 million on suicide and self-harm prevention research since the National Suicide Prevention Strategy to inform and target our strategy for reducing suicide rates.</p><p> </p><p>In January last year, we asked local areas to aspire to an ambition of zero suicides, to raise awareness around mental health and suicide prevention in particular.</p><p> </p><p>We are in the early stages of discussions about re-invigorating the National Strategy to drive local delivery. We are developing those plans for this, and will make an announcement shortly.</p><p> </p><p>The highest cause of death in young men and women in England is death through suicide, and rapid skilled response through a well-publicised access route is essential to reduce mortality. The NHS111 Mental Health Programme has been set up specifically to improve services and NHS England is working with Mind and the Telephone Helplines Partnership to develop a training course designed by people with lived experience specifically to support 111 call handlers deliver the best possible response in times of crisis.</p><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2016-02-11T16:17:19.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451310/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451310/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451310/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-02-08","Suicide","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps he plans to take to improve suicide prevention policies in response to the statistics on suicides in the UK, 2013 Registrations, published by the Office for National Statistics on 19 January 2016.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","26293"
