"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451562","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-02-11","<p>Average domestic gas prices fell by £37 during 2015, and all six major suppliers have announced a further reduction in their tariffs in recent months. This is a good start, but the Government expects all suppliers to pass on reductions in the costs of supplying energy to consumers. I have met all the major energy suppliers in recent months to make that point clear.</p><p> </p><p>The Competition and Markets Authority are nearing the end of their enquiry into the energy markets, and I look forward to their conclusions. I am determined to do whatever it takes to ensure markets work well for consumers.</p>","Hastings and Rye","Amber Rudd",,"2016-02-11T15:19:15.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451562/answer","Biography information for Amber Rudd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451562/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451562/answer",,,,,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-02-08","Energy: Prices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what steps she is taking to ensure that reductions in the wholesale price of energy are passed on to consumers.","false","Biography information for John Nicolson","East Dunbartonshire","John  Nicolson","903596"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451680","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-02-11","<p>We assess compliance annually for a range of pollutants covered by European directives for all UK zones, including Greater London. The latest compliance report <em>Air Pollution in the UK 2014</em> was published in September last year and is available on the UK-Air website:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://uk-air.defra.gov.uk/library/annualreport/viewonline?year=2014_issue_1" target="_blank">http://uk-air.defra.gov.uk/library/annualreport/viewonline?year=2014_issue_1</a></p><p> </p><p>The air quality plan we published in December last year sets out the measures we are taking to reduce levels of nitrogen dioxide in London. The plan is available on the GOV.UK website at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/air-quality-in-the-uk-plan-to-reduce-nitrogen-dioxide-emissions" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/air-quality-in-the-uk-plan-to-reduce-nitrogen-dioxide-emissions</a></p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2016-02-11T10:40:29.79Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451680/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451680/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/451680/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-02-08","Air Pollution: Greater London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what recent assessment she has made of air quality in London.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","903593"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450954","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-02-10","<p>The Official Receiver is currently delivering a safe and secure liquidation of SSI. Once that has been completed, the Government will work with local partners to understand the potential for the redevelopment of the site. The future use or uses of the site will be key in determining the level of remediation required.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-02-10T18:20:23.14Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450954/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450954/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450954/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-02-05","Regeneration: Redcar","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what assessment has been made of the potential cost of works to the former SSI steel works site on Teesside to prepare it for redevelopment.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","26058"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450955","Department for Transport","false","2016-02-10","<p>The Department for Transport does not assess the total number of people working in logistics and transportation who experience mental health problems.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-02-10T16:37:31.043Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450955/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450955/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450955/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-02-05","Transport: Mental Illness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will make an assessment of the number of people working in logistics and transportation who experience mental health problems.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","26059"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450956","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-02-10","<p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>Costs are being incurred by the Official Receiver who is currently delivering a safe and secure liquidation of SSI. The Government is providing the Official Receiver with an indemnity to ensure he is able to deliver that safe liquidation of SSI and the net costs will be clearer at the end of that process.</p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-02-10T18:18:52.04Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450956/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450956/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450956/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-02-05","Regeneration: Redcar","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what information his Department holds on the cost of maintaining and securing the former SSI steel works site on Teesside in its present condition.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","26066"
