"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450958","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-02-15","<p>The Universities and Colleges Admissions Service (UCAS) publishes data on application and entry rates for full-time undergraduate courses.</p><p> </p><p>The tables show the proportion of 18 year olds from disadvantaged backgrounds who applied to university by the main January deadline (application rate) and the proportion of 18 year olds that accepted a place during a UCAS application cycle (entry rate).</p><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="8"><p>Table 1: Application rates for English 18 year olds from POLAR3 quintile 1 areas (for entry in year)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2009</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2010</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2011</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2012</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2015</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2016</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>15.2%</p></td><td><p>18.0%</p></td><td><p>18.6%</p></td><td><p>17.9%</p></td><td><p>18.9%</p></td><td><p>20.4%</p></td><td><p>21.0%</p></td><td><p>22.0%</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="7"><p>Table 2: Entry rates for English 18 year olds from POLAR3 quintile 1 areas (for entry in year)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2009</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2010</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2011</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2012</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2015</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>13.6%</p></td><td><p>14.2%</p></td><td><p>15.1%</p></td><td><p>15.1%</p></td><td><p>16.4%</p></td><td><p>17.8%</p></td><td><p>18.5%</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p><strong>Notes:</strong></p><ol><li>Data published by UCAS covers full-time undergraduate applications. Table 1 shows the application rates by the main January deadline.</li><li>Data for entry rates in Table 2 include acceptances across the whole application cycle.</li><li>Disadvantage is measured by POLAR quintile 1 an area based measure of low participation.</li><li>Source of data for application rates: UCAS ‘<em>Application rates by the January Deadline</em>’ report for the 2016 cycle (underlying data for Figure 14) – published in February 2016.</li><li>Source of data for entry rates: UCAS ‘<em>2015 End of Cycle</em>’ report (underlying data for Figure 65) – published in December 2015.</li></ol><p><strong> </strong></p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-02-15T17:14:58.833Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450958/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450958/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450958/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-02-05","Universities: Admissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what estimate he has made of the proportion of young people from disadvantaged backgrounds who applied to university in each of the last six years.","false","Biography information for Ben Howlett","Bath","Ben Howlett","26081"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450959","HM Treasury","false","2016-02-15","<p><strong>The information to which Ministers have access is the same as that in the public domain.</strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) is responsible for the conduct of tax inquiries. Ministers are not privy to information about the individual tax arrangements of any company.</strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-02-15T12:50:25.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450959/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450959/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450959/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-02-05","Google: Tax Avoidance","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the contribution of the Financial Secretary to the Treasury of 3 February 2016, Official Report, column 975, what level of information has been disclosed to him in respect of Google's tax return and the HM Revenue and Customs agreement with that company.","false","Biography information for Caroline Flint","Don Valley","Caroline Flint","26082"
